  "title": "Senior Quantity Surveyor (Tender)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Understand the requirement of tender document</li>\n  <li>Exercise collaborative plan and define extend of works</li>\n  <li>Understand and deliver the job within timelines</li>\n  <li>Timely management of tender activities</li>\n  <li>General duty includes measurement of quantity, cost comparison and participate in prepare tender price</li>\n  <li>Review of quotations with the specification designed</li>\n  <li>Review of the quantity from each buddy, cross check for possible item that may have overlook</li>\n  <li>Participate in tender price build-up and analysis</li>\n  <li>Meeting and Discussion with Client, Consultant, Subcon, Specialist, etc.</li>\n  <li>Review of cost impact (Value Engineering proposal/ Variations)</li>\n  <li>Other tasks assigned by the Management</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma, Bachelor’s Degree or higher in Architecture / Structure / M&amp;E / Quantity Surveying</li>\n  <li>Minimum 5 years of experience in the construction industry, with a strong focus on project tendering</li>\n  <li>Strong knowledge of construction contracts, cost estimation, and tender submission processes</li>\n  <li>Proficient in Microsoft Excel, Glodon and tendering software</li>\n  <li>Ability to work under tight deadlines and manage multiple tenders simultaneously</li>\n  <li>Able to work independently and be a good team player as well.</li>\n  <li>Possess excellent people skills with the ability to integrate within a multi-disciplinary team and communicate.</li>\n</ul>",
